---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Course"
  description="Twilight Biathlon course: 5K two-lap route through Oklahoma fields, woods, and creek beds with four live-fire stages."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <p class="section-label">// Course</p>
    <h1
      class="mt-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-5xl font-bold uppercase sm:text-6xl"
    >
      Two laps. Four stages. No lights.
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg text-[var(--color-text)]/90 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        The course is a 5K two-lap route through Oklahoma fields, woods, and
        creek beds. Terrain is unlit, uneven, and tests navigation and light
        discipline as much as shooting fitness.
      </p>
      <p>
        Four live-fire stages sit along the route. An odd/even rotation splits
        competitors: even-number competitors run even stages on lap one and odd
        stages on lap two; odd-number competitors do the reverse. This is
        engineered to prevent bottlenecks at any single stage.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
        Course map graphic + stage diagrams go here once photography and course
        map assets are ready.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
